true}, "short_span_min_tokens": {"details": {"min_tokens": 2, "token_count": 78}, "passed": true}}, "text": "2. SOVIET OFFICIAL OUTLINES VIEWS ON NEAR EAST TO ISRAELI OFFICIAL\n\nComment\n\nMoscow's policy of playing down the Arab-Israeli dispute and its unwillingness to commit itself publicly to the Arab viewpoint on this issue was evidenced during Shepilov's tour of the Near East. In public, he avoided the question entirely and, in private, reportedly urged the Arabs to let time take care of the Palestine problem and expressed Soviet support for any UN move toward a peaceful settlement", "token_count": 78, "token_end_0based": 77, "token_start_0based": 0, "token_text": "2 soviet official outlines views on near east to israeli official comment moscow's policy of playing down the arab-israeli dispute and its unwillingness to commit itself publicly to the arab viewpoint on this issue was evidenced during shepilov's tour of the near east in public he avoided the question entirely and in private reportedly urged the arabs to let time take care of the palestine problem and expressed soviet support for any un move toward a peaceful settlement", "unred_source_page": 5}
